{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44056","id":1125335099,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM4yIzZ_","number":44056,"title":"Insert eager calls to `finalize` for otherwise-dead finalizeable objects","user":{"login":"jpsamaroo","id":17912843,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTEyODQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17912843?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo","html_url":"https://github.com/jpsamaroo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":195227131,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxOTUyMjcxMzE=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/GC","name":"GC","color":"009800","default":false,"description":"Garbage collector"},{"id":294535960,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyOTQ1MzU5NjA=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/needs%20tests","name":"needs tests","color":"5319e7","default":false,"description":"Unit tests are required for this change"},{"id":854410734,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw4NTQ0MTA3MzQ=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/optimizer","name":"optimizer","color":"55db9f","default":false,"description":"Optimization passes (mostly in base/compiler/ssair/)"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2022-02-06T22:23:03Z","updated_at":"2022-02-11T15:26:57Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/44056","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44056","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44056.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44056.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"Finalizers are a great way to defer the freeing side of memory management until some later point; however, they can have unpredictable behavior when the data that they free is not fully known to the GC (e.g. GPU allocations, or distributed references). This can result in behavior like out-of-memory situations, excessive memory usage, and sometimes more costly freeing behavior (in the event that locks need to be taken).

This seems like a bad situation, but there is a silver lining: some code patterns which allocate such objects don't actually need the allocations to stick around very long, and the lifetime of the object could (in theory) be statically determined by the compiler. Thankfully, with the ongoing work of integrating EscapeAnalysis.jl into the optimizer, we can use the generated escape information to improve this situation.

This PR uses escape info from EA to determine when an object has an attached finalizer, and when its lifetime is provably finite (i.e. the object does not escape the analyzed scope). For such objects, we can insert an early call to `finalize(obj)` at the end of `obj`'s lifetime, which will allow the object's finalizer to be enqueued for execution immediately, minimizing how long finalizeable object stay live in the GC.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056/reactions","total_count":13,"+1":5,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":8,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1036331395","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44056#issuecomment-1036331395","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44056","id":1036331395,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM49xSmD","user":{"login":"jpsamaroo","id":17912843,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTEyODQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17912843?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo","html_url":"https://github.com/jpsamaroo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpsamaroo/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-02-11T15:26:57Z","updated_at":"202